commit.message:
flatpak-proxy: Fix D-Bus disconnection with overly long object paths

According to the D-Bus specifications:
https://dbus.freedesktop.org/doc/dbus-specification.html#id-1.4.4
For the STRING and OBJECT_PATH types, [the data length] is encoded in 4
bytes (a UINT32).

But the code was trying to parse the 32-bit integer as an 8-bit one,
meaning that, as was the case with object paths created by the dLeyna
project, a 259-byte long string would be parsed like a 3-byte long
one.

Fixes: 004b7b2ca0e9 ("Parse dbus headers") in flatpak

flatpak-proxy: Print parsed header info when parsing fails

Print the parts of the header that got successfully parsed when parsing
fails.
flatpak-proxy: Add error reporting to string parsing

flatpak-proxy: Add error reporting to header parsing

When a header failed to parse, "Invalid message header format" was
printed without more details, making it impossible to debug problems in
the client(s).
flatpak-proxy: Rename error variable for future changes

meson: Optionally install tests for "as-installed" testing

This is used in the Debian packaging via ginsttest-runner and the
autopkgtest framework. Previously, it was supported by the Autotools
build system but not by the Meson build system.

commit.message:
build: Add switch warnings

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

build: Add some more compiler warnings

Taken from ostree, via bubblewrap.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

flatpak-proxy: Handle every case in a switch

This lets us use -Wswitch-enum to detect when we've missed one.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

flatpak-proxy: Move a case from an if() into a switch()

Instead of special-casing EXPECTED_REPLY_NONE to be a separate if()
block, treating it as part of the switch() lets us use -Wswitch-enum
to warn if we have missed one.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

flatpak-proxy: Silence compiler warnings about invalid casts

GSource and -Wcast-function-type don't really get on, but G_SOURCE_FUNC
has the appropriate magic to stop the compiler warning about this cast.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

buffer_read: Be more careful with signedness

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

dbus-proxy: Treat GPtrArray index as unsigned

This squashes some -Wsign-compare warnings.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

flatpak-proxy: Fix unintended fallthrough

If the reply to Hello() is an error (or some other non-reply), we don't
want to fall through to EXPECTED_REPLY_REWRITE. Treat it like
EXPECTED_REPLY_NORMAL instead.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>

Add an option to disable build-time tests

When using xdg-dbus-proxy as a subproject in Flatpak, we don't
necessarily want to run its unit tests as part of Flatpak's test
suite.

In particular, when bundling selected source code from xdg-dbus-proxy
into Flatpak `make dist` tarballs, it would be simpler if we could
avoid having to include the unit tests.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@collabora.com>
